##OUTBREAK IN SOUTH KOREA! The total number of confirmed cases increased to 763 and more than 7,700 soldiers were quarantined

Micro Signal China Business Journal

Function introduction, grow in step with Chinese enterprises, talk with business leaders, spread business ideals, serve business people, "China Business News" control of the absolute voice of Chinese business.

As of 9:00 am, 161 new cases of pneumonia had been confirmed in South Korea since 4:00 pm the previous day, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 763, with 7 deaths, according to a report from the Korean Central Epidemic Prevention Department on the 24th. According to South Korean media reports, a 16-month-old baby girl was diagnosed with infection, which is the youngest case of newly diagnosed pneumonia in South Korea.

South Korean President Moon jae-in on the afternoon of the 23rd announced his decision to raise the alert level of the epidemic to the highest "serious" level, significantly strengthening the epidemic prevention response system.

Eleven soldiers confirmed! 7,700 quarantined

South Korea's Defense Ministry said 11 soldiers had contracted COVID-19 pneumonia as of Monday morning, and more than 7,700 were being quarantined to prevent the disease spreading to military camps, Yonhap reported.

On Feb. 23, South Korean military data showed that seven people were confirmed, the Defense Ministry said. By 8 a.m. on Feb. 24, the number had risen to 11, with eight confirmed in the army and one each in the navy, Air Force and Marine Corps.

According to an officer, four newly confirmed soldiers were suspected to have contracted the virus after coming into contact with a confirmed patient in the barracks. South Korean military reported the first confirmed case on the 21st.

Most of the confirmed cases are in Taegu and North Gyeongsang Province, according to official reports. The Seoul Metropolitan Government called an emergency meeting on Sunday to urge police departments to cooperate with the government, limit assemblies and prevent the spread of the epidemic, and said they would report the epidemic on a daily basis and temporarily close many public facilities, twenty-five health centres ceased general medical services and operated "screening clinics" on a 24-hour basis.

Seoul Mayor Park Won-soon said that in the face of the severe situation of the epidemic, Seoul should take "pre-emptive" strong measures, has established an emergency response mechanism, some hospitals are being converted or added to use isolation ward to ensure medical resources.

Anchorwoman sent to hospital with fever at work: Programme cancelled

South Korea's JTBC TV meteorologist Kim Min-ah was taken to hospital Tuesday with a low grade fever and tested for the new coronavirus, Yonhap News Agency reported. It has been quarantined, and its news program, "MORNING & , " which it recorded, was abruptly canceled on the 24th.

JTBC television also said that, just in case, "morning & " all the members of the program, are also self-isolation. "TV operators have a wide range of activities and a large number of contacts, which are measures that have to be taken. ".

South Korea raises alert for new pneumonia to highest level

According to Xinhua News Agency, South Korean President Moon jae-in announced on the afternoon of the 23rd that the government had decided to raise the crisis alert level of the new coronavirus infectious disease to the highest "serious" level on the advice of infectious disease experts, significantly strengthening the epidemic prevention and Response System.

Moon said the situation in South Korea now faces a "major watershed" in the coming days, with the government taking "unprecedented and strong measures to deal with it. ". He said the South Korean government should continue to maintain a disease prevention system centered on the Ministry of Disease Management, while strengthening the role of the Central Disaster Safety Response Department, chaired by the Prime Minister, and strengthening the response of government departments, further increase the central government's support to local governments.

South Korea's infectious disease early warning is divided into "attention" , "attention" , "alert" and "serious" four levels. After issuing a "serious" warning, the government can take the highest level of response measures, including ordering all levels of schools closed, banned collective activities. South Korean government decided on the 23rd, the national kindergarten, primary and secondary schools and other levels of the 2020 school year start date a week, from March 2 to March 9.

South Korea's Ministry of Education Eases credit limit for students who drop out of school this semester

On February 24, the Chinese Embassy in South Korea reminded Chinese students studying in South Korea:

1 before entering the country: be sure to contact the Korean institutions;

2 On arrival: 23rd to 29th is designated as "Centralized Management Week" , Chinese students are required to confirm their health status according to special entry procedures and install "self-diagnosis application (special APP) " on mobile phones;

3 after arrival: self-isolation 14 days, through a special APP with the school daily report.

4 South Korea's Ministry of Education said it would relax the credit limit for international students who drop out of school this semester, and encourage universities to sign mutual credit agreements to facilitate Chinese students taking courses from other schools online while they are in China.

15 countries and territories impose immigration controls on Korea

South Korea's Foreign Ministry said Monday it would step up quarantine efforts as more and more countries and regions impose border controls as the COVID-19 outbreak spreads across the country, Yonhap News Agency reported.

To date, 15 countries and regions have banned or strengthened entry control measures for persons from the Republic of Korea. Six countries, Israel, Bahrain, Jordan, Kiribati, Samoa and the American Samoa, have banned foreigners who have visited South Korea for 14 days, or those who have stayed in the zone for 14 days for health checks.

Chinese Embassy in South Korea reminds Chinese citizens to strengthen self-protection

The South Korean government has raised the alert to the highest level of "serious" and designated the Daegu and North Gyeongsang Province areas as "special control areas" , the Chinese embassy said in a statement today. The South Korean government will increase its response, depending on the circumstances, including ordering the closure of schools, prohibiting assembly and other measures.

The Chinese Embassy in the Republic of Korea reminds Chinese citizens in the Republic of Korea: 1 avoid going to crowded areas and special control areas designated by the ROK side. Go out to wear a mask, wash hands frequently, frequently disinfection, frequently ventilation. 2 If fever or other suspected symptoms, should avoid going out or contact with others, timely call Korea Disease Management Headquarters 1339(with Chinese Service) for diagnosis and treatment. It is suggested that all overseas Chinese delegations cancel large-scale activities such as gatherings and dinners. 4 Scientific Response, active prevention, avoid panic, do not believe rumors, do not spread rumors.
